# Secrets and Sensitive Configuration Audit

k8s-forge examples must not include real sensitive values. Generated readiness files are educational and should use placeholders only.

## Review points

- No real sensitive value should be committed in app configuration or generated files.
- Placeholders are acceptable for labs, but production values need a separate lifecycle.
- Kubernetes Secret objects are base64-encoded data containers; encryption at rest depends on cluster configuration.
- Avoid putting sensitive key material in generated examples.
- Prefer external secret management patterns such as sealed-secrets, external-secrets, or Vault-style workflows when moving beyond the lab.

This file does not inspect live Secret objects and does not validate cluster encryption settings.
